div.font: Leverage metadata-driven control framework for orchestration, modeling, table maintenance, data refresh, and logging activities.

font.div: Read/copy data from source system using Spark via notebook, pipeline, or shortcut.

div.font: Use managed private endpoints or on-premise data gateway when working with on-premise or firewall enabled source systems.
Store data in lakehouse as close to raw form as possible.
Transform and prepare data using Spark notebooks. Notebooks provide flexibility for developers to use the language native to them (PySpark, SparkSQL, etc.).
Copy data to warehouse using pipeline (optional).
Transform and prepare data using warehouse SQL analytics endpoint. Create shortcut from warehouse to lakehouse (optional).

div.span: Sync development workspace to git repo in Azure DevOps to commit changes and establish source control.

span.font: Feature branches can be created for isolated development workspaces enabling multi-developer workloads.
Content creators clone remote repo to local development environment to capture latest working version.
Commit local development changes to git repo and create pull request to merge changes from feature branch to main branch.

div.font: Completing a pull request willtrigger the Test / Validate that performs automated tests to validate content before being published.

span.font: Build pipeline is then triggered to prepare content for deployment.
Deployment to test and production is facilitated by the release pipeline.
Release to higher environment is gated by a release manager approval(s).
Release pipeline performs deployment from dev. to test by triggering the Fabric deployment pipeline.
Testing and QA is performed prior to being released to prod.

font.span: Release pipeline performs deployment form test to prod.
by triggering the Fabric deployment pipeline.
